culture created an ideology of power focused on a single individual, celebrating his military prowess, investing him with divine authority, and creating a figure instantly recognizable to readers of Homer and students of Greek history. A Greek State in Formation makes the powerful case that a knowledge of the Greek Bronze Age is indispensable to the classics curriculum.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Greece.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022 Englishz978311099291508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022z9783110992878oZDB-23-DGD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107664930 cprintz978052038724940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780520387256?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520387256zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520387256/original  a978-3-11-076649-3 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099291-5 EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGDb2022  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-UCY